dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5466  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"ATP-sensitive potassium (K_ATP) channels in neuron and neuroendocrine cells consist of a pore-forming Kir6.2 (gene KCNJ11) and regulatory sulfonylurea receptor (SUR1, gene ABCC8) subunits, which are regulated by ATP and ADP.\"\n\nFigure 1: Syntaxin-1A (STX1A) inhibits K_ATP channels in HIT-T15 cells.\n\nFigure 2: pulldown of overexpressed GST-Syntaxin1a from solubilized rat brain synaptic membranes yields SUR1 (ABCC8). The major cytoplasmic domains of SUR1 are NBF-1 (aa 696-893) and C-terminal NBF-2 (aa 1358-1544). GST-NBF-1 and GST-NBF-2 bound to agarose beads pulled down native Syntaxin1A from rat brain synaptic membranes.\n\n\"To negate the possibility of a coprecipitation of unknown ternary proteins present in the brain, we demonstrated that GST-NBF-1 and GST-NBF-2 pulled down recombinant Syn-1A but not control GST or recombinant SNAP-25 (data not shown).\"\n\nFigure 3, 4: functional characterization of the Syntaxin-1A and SUR1 interaction in pancreatic islet β-cells. Syntaxin-1A Inhibition of the KATP Channel Is Mediated by Its Binding to NBF-1.. Experimental description: Results: \"GST-Syn-1A bound to agarose beads pulled down SUR1 from solubilized rat brain synaptic membranes\"\n\n\"specific antibody generated against the SUR1 C terminus\" PMID:10373428" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5466" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

